3.4:
May that day be darkness;
May God above not care for it,
Nor light shine on it.

3.5:
May darkness and black gloom claim it;
May a cloud settle on it;
May the blackness of the day terrify it.

3.6:
As for that night, may darkness seize it;
May it not rejoice among the days of the year;
May it not come into the number of the months.

3.9:
May the stars of its twilight be darkened;
May it wait for light but have none,
And may it not see the breaking dawn;

4.16:
Something was standing still, but I could not recognize its appearance;
A form was before my eyes;
There was silence, then I heard a voice:

6.4:
For the arrows of the Almighty are within me,
My spirit drinks their poison;
The terrors of God line up against me.

7.11:
“Therefore I will not restrain my mouth;
I will speak in the anguish of my spirit,
I will complain in the bitterness of my soul.

9.21:
I am guiltless;
I do not take notice of myself;
I reject my life.

9.24:
The earth is handed over to the wicked;
He covers the faces of its judges.
If it is not He, then who is it?

10.1:
“I am disgusted with my own life;
I will express my complaint freely;
I will speak in the bitterness of my soul.

10.17:
You renew Your witnesses against me
And increase Your anger toward me;
Hardship after hardship is with me.

11.20:
But the eyes of the wicked will fail,
And there will be no escape for them;
And their hope is to breathe their last.”

12.3:
But I have intelligence as well as you;
I am not inferior to you.
And who does not know such things as these?

12.4:
I am a joke to my friends,
The one who called on God and He answered him;
The just and blameless man is a joke.

13.27:
You put my feet in the stocks
And watch all my paths;
You set a limit for the soles of my feet,

14.5:
Since his days are determined,
The number of his months is with You;
And You have set his limits so that he cannot pass.

14.19:
Water wears away stones,
Its torrents wash away the dust of the earth;
So You destroy a man’s hope.

15.30:
He will not escape from darkness;
The flame will dry up his shoot,
And he will go away by the breath of His mouth.

16.9:
His anger has torn me and hunted me down,
He has gnashed at me with His teeth;
My enemy glares at me.

16.10:
They have gaped at me with their mouths,
They have slapped me on the cheek with contempt;
They have massed themselves against me.

16.12:
I was at ease, but He shattered me,
And He has grasped me by my neck and shaken me to pieces;
He has also set me up as His target.

16.13:
His arrows surround me.
He splits my kidneys open without mercy;
He pours out my bile on the ground.

20.15:
He swallows riches,
But will vomit them up;
God will expel them from his belly.

20.25:
It is drawn and comes out of his back,
Even the flashing point from his gallbladder;
Terrors come upon him,

20.26:
Complete darkness is held in reserve for his treasures,
And unfanned fire will devour him;
It will consume the survivor in his tent.

21.33:
The clods of the valley will gently cover him;
Moreover, all mankind will follow after him,
While countless others go before him.

24.12:
From the city people groan,
And the souls of the wounded cry for help;
Yet God does not pay attention to the offensiveness.

24.13:
“Others have been with those who rebel against the light;
They do not want to know its ways
Nor stay in its paths.

24.14:
The murderer arises at dawn;
He kills the poor and the needy,
And at night he is like a thief.

24.16:
In the darkness they dig into houses,
They shut themselves up by day;
They do not know the light.

24.18:
“They are insignificant on the surface of the water;
Their plot of land on the earth is cursed.
They do not turn toward the vineyards.

24.20:
A mother will forget him;
The maggot feeds sweetly until he is no longer remembered.
And injustice will be broken like a tree.

24.24:
They are exalted a little while, then they are gone;
Moreover, they are brought low, and like everything they are gathered up;
Like the heads of grain they wither.

26.14:
Behold, these are the fringes of His ways;
And how faint a word we hear of Him!
But His mighty thunder, who can understand?”

28.4:
He sinks a shaft away from inhabited areas,
Forgotten by the foot;
They hang and swing, away from people.

30.13:
They break up my path,
They promote my destruction;
No one restrains them.

30.15:
Sudden terrors are turned upon me;
They chase away my dignity like the wind,
And my prosperity has passed away like a cloud.

32.6:
So Elihu the son of Barachel the Buzite spoke out and said,
“I am young in years and you are old;
Therefore I was shy and afraid to tell you what I think.

32.12:
I also paid close attention to you;
But indeed, there was no one who refuted Job,
Not one of you who answered his words.

33.24:
And he is gracious to him, and says,
‘Free him from going down to the pit,
I have found a ransom’;

34.31:
“For has anyone said to God,
‘I have endured punishment;
I will not offend anymore;

34.32:
Teach me what I do not see;
If I have done wrong,
I will not do it again’?

34.33:
Shall God repay on your terms, because you have rejected His?
For you must choose, and not I;
Therefore declare what you know.

34.37:
For he adds rebellion to his sin;
He claps his hands among us,
And multiplies his words against God.’”

36.16:
Then indeed, He induced you away from the mouth of distress,
And instead of it, a broad place with no constraint;
And your table was full of rich food.

37.4:
After it, a voice roars;
He thunders with His majestic voice,
And He does not restrain the lightning when His voice is heard.

37.23:
The Almighty—we cannot find Him;
He is exalted in power
And He will not violate justice and abundant righteousness.
